Key Match Events: De'Aaron Fox scored 49 points and had nine assists in the Sacramento Kings' 121-117 victory over the Utah Jazz.
The Kings had to claw back from an 11-point deficit to secure the win.
Jazz rookie Kyle Filipowski effectively defended against De'Aaron Fox, causing Fox to miss both shot attempts when matched up against him.
Post-Match Reflections: Jazz head coach Will Hardy praised Kyle Filipowski's defensive performance, noting his ability to switch and defend smaller players.
Collin Sexton had a positive outlook on the numerous game stoppages, viewing them as opportunities for the team to regroup and communicate.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game lasted 2 hours and 35 minutes, with the final two minutes taking more than 20 minutes of real time due to numerous stoppages and reviews.
